dlinkSwIpExtMIB.name: dlinkSwIpExtMIB

revisions.description: 1.Remove dIpExtDhcpClientIfRowStatus(Note:follow IP interface). 2.Update dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseDay value range(Note:follow UIS).

dlinkSwIpExtMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwIpExtMIB.description: This MIB is an extension to the standard IP-MIB.

dIpExtGratuitousARPTrap.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPTrap
dIpExtGratuitousARPTrap.description: This trap is sent when there is an IP address conflict.

dIpExtClearArpCacheAll.name: dIpExtClearArpCacheAll
dIpExtClearArpCacheAll.description: This object is used to clear all dynamic ARP entries from the table when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dIpExtClearArpCacheByIf.name: dIpExtClearArpCacheByIf
dIpExtClearArpCacheByIf.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the interface on which the dynamic ARP entries will be cleared. When read, a value of 0 is returned.

dIpExtTotalArpEntries.name: dIpExtTotalArpEntries
dIpExtTotalArpEntries.description: This object indicates the total number of ARP entries.

dIpExtGratuitousARPSendRequestEnabled.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPSendRequestEnabled
dIpExtGratuitousARPSendRequestEnabled.description: This object is used to enable/disable transmission of gratuitous ARP request. The device will send out the packet when an IP interface becomes link up or when the IP address of an interface is configured or modified.

dIpExtGratuitousARPLearningEnabled.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPLearningEnabled
dIpExtGratuitousARPLearningEnabled.description: This object is used to enable/disable learning of an ARP entry in the ARP cache based on the received gratuitous ARP packet. If the device receives a gratuitous ARP request/reply packet and the sender's IP address is in its ARP table, it should update the ARP entry.

dIpExtGratuitousARPDadReplyEnabled.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPDadReplyEnabled
dIpExtGratuitousARPDadReplyEnabled.description: This object is used to enable/disable sending of gratuitous ARP request while duplicate IP address is detected.

dIpExtGratuitousARPTrapEnabled.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPTrapEnabled
dIpExtGratuitousARPTrapEnabled.description: This indicates the state of the gratuitous ARP trap. The switch can trap the IP conflict events to inform the administrator. By default, the trap is disabled.

dIpExtGratuitousARPIpAddr.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPIpAddr
dIpExtGratuitousARPIpAddr.description: A duplicate IP address with the switch already exists.

dIpExtGratuitousARPMacAddr.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPMacAddr
dIpExtGratuitousARPMacAddr.description: This object is the MAC address of the device which has the duplicate IP address.

dIpExtGratuitousARPPortNumber.name: dIpExtGratuitousARPPortNumber
dIpExtGratuitousARPPortNumber.description: This object is the the port number.

dIpExtClearAllIpv6Neighbors.name: dIpExtClearAllIpv6Neighbors
dIpExtClearAllIpv6Neighbors.description: This object is used to clear dynamic neighbor cache entries associated with all interfaces when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dIpExtClearIpv6NeighborsByIf.name: dIpExtClearIpv6NeighborsByIf
dIpExtClearIpv6NeighborsByIf.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the interface on which the dynamic neighbor cache entries will be cleared. When read, a value of 0 is returned.

dIpExtTotalIpv6Neighbors.name: dIpExtTotalIpv6Neighbors
dIpExtTotalIpv6Neighbors.description: This object indicates the total number of dynamic neighbor cache entries.

dIpExtIpIfTable.name: dIpExtIpIfTable
dIpExtIpIfTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to create or delete layer 3 interfaces. It is expected that user first creates a row in this table, followed by configuring the row in dIpExtIfCfgTable via the corresponding ifIndex.

dIpExtIpIfEntry.name: dIpExtIpIfEntry
dIpExtIpIfEntry.description: A row instance contains the information of the layer 3 interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable.

dIpExtIpIfType.name: dIpExtIpIfType
dIpExtIpIfType.description: This object indicates the type of the interface. 'loopback' - The software only interface which always stays in up status. 'vlan' - VLAN interface.

dIpExtIpIfNumber.name: dIpExtIpIfNumber
dIpExtIpIfNumber.description: This object indicates the interface ID within the type.

dIpExtIpIfIndex.name: dIpExtIpIfIndex
dIpExtIpIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface is determined by the agent.

dIpExtIpIfRowStatus.name: dIpExtIpIfRowStatus
dIpExtIpIfRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dIpExtIfCfgTableNumber.name: dIpExtIfCfgTableNumber
dIpExtIfCfgTableNumber.description: Indicates the number of entries present in the dIpExtIfCfgTable.

dIpExtIfCfgTable.name: dIpExtIfCfgTable
dIpExtIfCfgTable.description: A table contains extended per-interface information.

dIpExtIfCfgEntry.name: dIpExtIfCfgEntry
dIpExtIfCfgEntry.description: A row in this table is created as a side effect of row addition in the dIpExtIpIfTable.

dIpExtIfCfgIfIndex.name: dIpExtIfCfgIfIndex
dIpExtIfCfgIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface.

dIpExtIfCfgDhcpEnabled.name: dIpExtIfCfgDhcpEnabled
dIpExtIfCfgDhcpEnabled.description: The object indicates whether acquire an IP address configuration on the interface from the DHCP protocol.

dIpExtIfCfgArpTimeout.name: dIpExtIfCfgArpTimeout
dIpExtIfCfgArpTimeout.description: This object indicates the ARP aging time in unit of minute for dynamic ARP entries on the corresponding interface. Setting this variable to 0 the ARP entries will not be aged out.

dIpExtIfCfgProxyArpEnabled.name: dIpExtIfCfgProxyArpEnabled
dIpExtIfCfgProxyArpEnabled.description: The object indicates the state of proxy ARP on the corresponding interface.

dIpExtIfCfgLocalProxyArpEnabled.name: dIpExtIfCfgLocalProxyArpEnabled
dIpExtIfCfgLocalProxyArpEnabled.description: The object indicates the state of local proxy ARP on the corresponding interface.

dIpExtIfCfgDirectedBcastEnabled.name: dIpExtIfCfgDirectedBcastEnabled
dIpExtIfCfgDirectedBcastEnabled.description: The object indicates the state of the conversion of IP directed broadcasts on the corresponding interface.

dIpExtIfCfgDirectedBcastAcl.name: dIpExtIfCfgDirectedBcastAcl
dIpExtIfCfgDirectedBcastAcl.description: The object indicates the name of a standard IP access list.

dIpExtIfCfgGratuitousARPSendInterval.name: dIpExtIfCfgGratuitousARPSendInterval
dIpExtIfCfgGratuitousARPSendInterval.description: This object indicates the interval of regularly sending the gratuitous ARP request message in unit of second on the corresponding interface. A value of zero indicates the gratuitous ARP will not be regularly sent.

dIpExtIfCfgIpMtu.name: dIpExtIfCfgIpMtu
dIpExtIfCfgIpMtu.description: The MTU is the largest size of the IP datagram which may be transferred using a specific data link connection. The MTU value is a design parameter of a LAN and is a mutually agreed value (i.e. both ends of a link agree to use the same specific value) for most WAN links. The MTU range is based on the chip of the current device.

dIpExtIfCfgDADTransmits.name: dIpExtIfCfgDADTransmits
dIpExtIfCfgDADTransmits.description: This object indicates the number of Neighbor Solicitations to send during Duplicate Address Detection (DAD). A value of zero indicates DAD is disabled.

dIpExtIpAddressTable.name: dIpExtIpAddressTable
dIpExtIpAddressTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to this entity's IP addresses. This is the enhancement of the ipAddressTable in IP-MIB. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries be created/deleted in ipAddressTable.

dIpExtIpAddressEntry.name: dIpExtIpAddressEntry
dIpExtIpAddressEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this entity's IP addresses.

dIpExtIpAddressType.name: dIpExtIpAddressType
dIpExtIpAddressType.description: The Internet address type of entry.

dIpExtIpAddress.name: dIpExtIpAddress
dIpExtIpAddress.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

dIpExtIpAddressIfIndex.name: dIpExtIpAddressIfIndex
dIpExtIpAddressIfIndex.description: The ifindex value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

dIpExtIpAddressPrefixLength.name: dIpExtIpAddressPrefixLength
dIpExtIpAddressPrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix associated with the IP address of this entry.

dIpExtIpAddressCategory.name: dIpExtIpAddressCategory
dIpExtIpAddressCategory.description: This object indicates the IP address category of this entry. The 'primary' and 'secondary' are valid for IPv4 address. Although multiple IPv4 addresses can be created for an interface, at most one of these addresses is the primary IPv4 address, and the rest are secondary IPv4 address. 'linkLocal' and 'eui64' are valid for IPv6 address. 'linkLocal' - The IPv6 address is a link local address. 'eui64' - The IPv6 address is formed by EUI-64 interface ID. The corresponding prefix length must be smaller than 64.

dIpExtIpAddressRowStatus.name: dIpExtIpAddressRowStatus
dIpExtIpAddressRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage creation and deletion of rows in this table.

dIpExtIpAddrBaseGenPrefixTable.name: dIpExtIpAddrBaseGenPrefixTable
dIpExtIpAddrBaseGenPrefixTable.description: This table allows the configuration of IPv6 address based on a general prefix.

dIpExtIpAddrBaseGenPrefixEntry.name: dIpExtIpAddrBaseGenPrefixEntry
dIpExtIpAddrBaseGenPrefixEntry.description: This object indicates the association of general prefix for configuring IPv6 address on an interface.

dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixIfIndex.name: dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixIfIndex
dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixIfIndex.description: The ifindex value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixName.name: dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixName
dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixName.description: This object indicates the general prefix name which will be used to configure the IPv6 address on the interface.

dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixSubBits.name: dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixSubBits
dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixSubBits.description: This object indicates the sub-prefix part and host part of the IPv6 address.

dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixLength.name: dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixLength
dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix associated with the IP address of this entry.

dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixRowStatus.name: dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixRowStatus
dIpExtIpAddrBasePrefixRowStatus.description: This object is used to manage creation and deletion of rows in this table.

dIpExtIpv6GneralPrefixTable.name: dIpExtIpv6GneralPrefixTable
dIpExtIpv6GneralPrefixTable.description: This table allows the creation and removal of IPv6 general prefixes.

dIpExtIpv6GneralPrefixEntry.name: dIpExtIpv6GneralPrefixEntry
dIpExtIpv6GneralPrefixEntry.description: An entry consists of information of an IPv6 general prefix.

dIpExtGneralPrefixName.name: dIpExtGneralPrefixName
dIpExtGneralPrefixName.description: The ifindex value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

dIpExtGneralPrefixType.name: dIpExtGneralPrefixType
dIpExtGneralPrefixType.description: This object indicates the type of the prefix configuration. 'normal' - This general prefix is configured by dIpExtGneralPrefix and dIpExtGneralPrefixLength. 'ipv6ToIpv4' - The general prefix is configured by the interface (dIpExtGeneralPrefix6to4IfIndex) whose IPv4 address will be used to form a general prefix used for 6to4 tunnel.

dIpExtGneralPrefix.name: dIpExtGneralPrefix
dIpExtGneralPrefix.description: This object indicates the prefix of the entry. This object is meaningless when dIpExtGneralPrefixType is not 'normal'.

dIpExtGneralPrefixLength.name: dIpExtGneralPrefixLength
dIpExtGneralPrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix associated with the general prefix of this entry. This object is meaningless when dIpExtGneralPrefixType is not 'normal'.

dIpExtGeneralPrefix6to4IfIndex.name: dIpExtGeneralPrefix6to4IfIndex
dIpExtGeneralPrefix6to4IfIndex.description: This object indicates ifIndex of the interface whose IPv4 address will be used to form a general prefix used for 6to4 tunnel. This object is meaningless when dIpExtGneralPrefixType is not 'ipv6ToIpv4'.

dIpExtGeneralPrefixRowStatus.name: dIpExtGeneralPrefixRowStatus
dIpExtGeneralPrefixRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of IPv6 general prefixes.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixTable.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixTable
dIpExtIpv6PrefixTable.description: This table allows the creation and removal of IPv6 prefixes to be placed in Prefix Information options in Router Advertisement messages sent from the interface. This is the enhancement of the ipAddressPrefixTable in IP-MIB.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixIfIndex.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixIfIndex
dIpExtIpv6PrefixIfIndex.description: The ifindex value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixLength.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixLength
dIpExtIpv6PrefixLength.description: The prefix length of the entry.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixValidLifetime.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixValidLifetime
dIpExtIpv6PrefixValidLifetime.description: This object indicates the valid life time in seconds of the entry. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixPreferLifetime.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixPreferLifetime
dIpExtIpv6PrefixPreferLifetime.description: This object indicates the preferred life time in seconds of the entry. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixOnLinkFlag.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixOnLinkFlag
dIpExtIpv6PrefixOnLinkFlag.description: This object has the value 'true(1)', if this prefix can be used for on-link determination; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'. The default for IPv4 prefixes is 'true(1)'.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixAutonomousFlag.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixAutonomousFlag
dIpExtIpv6PrefixAutonomousFlag.description: Autonomous address configuration flag. When true(1), indicates that this prefix can be used for autonomous address configuration (i.e., can be used to form a local interface address). If false(2), it is not used to auto- configure a local interface address. The default for IPv4 prefixes is 'false(2)'.

dIpExtIpv6PrefixRowStatus.name: dIpExtIpv6PrefixRowStatus
dIpExtIpv6PrefixRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of IPv6 interface prefixes for RA messages.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfTable.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfTable
dIpExtDhcpClientIfTable.description: A table contains a list of DHCP client configuration of interfaces.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfEntry.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfEntry
dIpExtDhcpClientIfEntry.description: An entry is created to configure DHCP client per-interface settings to different value from default value. When an entry is deleted, all the settings are reverted to default value.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfIndex.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfIndex
dIpExtDhcpClientIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface. Only VLAN interfaces are valid interfaces.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdType.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdType
dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdType.description: The object indicates the type of class id which is defined by dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdValue. The value means : ascii(1)- The dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdValue is ascii string. hex(2) - The dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdValue is a string of HEX number.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdValue.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdValue
dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdValue.description: This object indicates the value of vendor class identifier (option 60) to be sent with the DHCP DISCOVER message. An dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdValue value is always interpreted within the context of an dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdType value. If dIpExtDhcpClientIfClassIdType is 'hex', this object is a HEX string value, which is restricted to hexadecimal character set.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfClientIdIfIdx.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfClientIdIfIdx
dIpExtDhcpClientIfClientIdIfIdx.description: This object indicates ifIndex of the VLAN interface whose hexadecimal MAC address will be used as the client ID to be sent with the DISCOVER message.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfHostName.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfHostName
dIpExtDhcpClientIfHostName.description: This object indicates the host name. The host name must start with a letter, end with a letter or digit, and only with interior characters letters, digits, and hyphens.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseDay.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseDay
dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseDay.description: This object indicates the number of days for the duration of preferred lease time. Value of -1 indicates that preferred lease time is unspecified. This value is checked when an IP address is acquired from a DHCP server.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseHour.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseHour
dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseHour.description: This object indicates the number of hours for the duration of preferred lease time.

dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseMinute.name: dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseMinute
dIpExtDhcpClientIfLeaseMinute.description: This object indicates the number of minutes for the duration of preferred lease time.

dIpExtDhcpClientAutoconfig.name: dIpExtDhcpClientAutoconfig
dIpExtDhcpClientAutoconfig.description: Indicates the status of automatically getting the configuration information from a TFTP server connected to the device.

dIpExtUdpFwdPortTable.name: dIpExtUdpFwdPortTable
dIpExtUdpFwdPortTable.description: This table consists of a list of UDP ports to forward UDP packets.

dIpExtUdpFwdPortEntry.name: dIpExtUdpFwdPortEntry
dIpExtUdpFwdPortEntry.description: An entry is created/deleted to enable/disable forwarding of a specific UDP service type of packets.

dIpExtUdpFwdPortNumber.name: dIpExtUdpFwdPortNumber
dIpExtUdpFwdPortNumber.description: The UDP port number of the entry.

dIpExtUdpFwdPortRowStatus.name: dIpExtUdpFwdPortRowStatus
dIpExtUdpFwdPortRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dIpExtUdpHelperAddrTable.name: dIpExtUdpHelperAddrTable
dIpExtUdpHelperAddrTable.description: This table consists of a list of target addresses for forwarding of UDP broadcast packets.

dIpExtUdpHelperAddrEntry.name: dIpExtUdpHelperAddrEntry
dIpExtUdpHelperAddrEntry.description: An target IP address for forwarding of the UDP broadcast packet on an interface.

dIpExtUdpHelperIfIndex.name: dIpExtUdpHelperIfIndex
dIpExtUdpHelperIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface on which the entry is configured. Only VLAN interfaces are valid interfaces.

dIpExtUdpHelperAddrType.name: dIpExtUdpHelperAddrType
dIpExtUdpHelperAddrType.description: The address type of UDP helper address.

dIpExtUdpHelperAddr.name: dIpExtUdpHelperAddr
dIpExtUdpHelperAddr.description: An IP address of the server.

dIpExtUdpHelperAddrRowStatus.name: dIpExtUdpHelperAddrRowStatus
dIpExtUdpHelperAddrRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dIpExtCompliance.name: dIpExtCompliance
dIpExtCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the DLINKSW-IP-EXT-MIB.

dIpExtBasicGroup.name: dIpExtBasicGroup
dIpExtBasicGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to IP/ARP settings which are not covered by standard IP-MIB.

dIpExtBasicIpv6OnlyGroup.name: dIpExtBasicIpv6OnlyGroup
dIpExtBasicIpv6OnlyGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to fundamental IPv6 feature.

dIpExtGeneralPrefixGroup.name: dIpExtGeneralPrefixGroup
dIpExtGeneralPrefixGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to general prefix configuration.

dIpExtRaPrefixGroup.name: dIpExtRaPrefixGroup
dIpExtRaPrefixGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to the configuration of IPv6 prefix which are advertised in RA.

dIpExtGratuitousArpGroup.name: dIpExtGratuitousArpGroup
dIpExtGratuitousArpGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to Gratuitous ARP feature.

dIpExtProxyArpGroup.name: dIpExtProxyArpGroup
dIpExtProxyArpGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to Proxy ARP.

dIpExtDirectedBroadcastGroup.name: dIpExtDirectedBroadcastGroup
dIpExtDirectedBroadcastGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to IP directed broadcasts feature.

dIpExtDhcpClientGroup.name: dIpExtDhcpClientGroup
dIpExtDhcpClientGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to DHCP client.

dIpExtUdpForwardGroup.name: dIpExtUdpForwardGroup
dIpExtUdpForwardGroup.description: This group contains the collection of objects related to UDP forwarding feature.
